thread.title: Jr. Cats prevail

title: Jr. Cats prevail
text: By The Union Democrat Sports Department October 20, 2015 01:00 am The Sonora Jr. Cats celebrate after beating the Tuolumne Bears. Guy Dossi / Union Democrat, Copyright 2015. The Sonora Jr. Cats varsity youth football team defeated the Tuolumne Bears 40-16 Saturday at Thorsted Field. The Jr. Cats (4-1) finished tied for first in the Motherlode division of the Motherlode Valley Football League while the Bears (2-3) placed fourth. Follow UnionDemocrat.com
